<item>
            <title>[LU-3272] block rename for FID_SEQ_DOT_LUSTRE, unify weird FID handling</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3272</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3245&quot; title=&quot;FS root OBF regression&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3245&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3245&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Andreas said &quot;Moving forward beyond the 6209 patch landing, it makes sense to explicitly block rename for the FID_SEQ_DOT_LUSTRE objects, since I don&apos;t think it ever makes sense to allow that.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should also review the other reint handlers checking for consistency with respect to the weird FIDs and, I hope, factor the cases into one or more &quot;client may access this FID for R/W/X/...&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
